Facebook appears to be rolling out new facial recognition functionality around the world, and is sending notices to users outside the EU and Canada, Neowin reported. This follows an announcement that Facebook will give users more control over where photos of them are used. It said the new facial recognition features will be available everywhere except Europe and Canada. Privacy regulators in those regions have raised objections to Facebook’s auto photo tagging feature. According to Facebook, it’s facial recognition features will: “We want people to feel confident when they post pictures of themselves on Facebook,” it previously stated. “We’re doing this to prevent people from impersonating others on Facebook.”